I'm sorry, but I can't create or upload image files. However, I can guide you on how to set an image as a background for a webpage using HTML and CSS.

Here's an example of how you can do it:

1. Save your image as `background.jpg` in the `public` directory of your project.

2. Create an HTML file (e.g., `index.html`) and add the following code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Home Page</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-image: url('public/background.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center;
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            height: 100vh;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to the Home Page</h1>
</body>
</html>
```

This code sets the `background.jpg` image as the background for the home page, ensuring it covers the entire viewport and is centered.